// The Bengali/English edition of the field reference. Same facing-pair design as the other
// editions: the Bengali take of each card sits on the left (verso) page and the matching English
// take on the right (recto). Bengali is LTR, set in the bundled Noto Serif Bengali face via
// \font bengali. The English cards are the same text as the other editions.

// Scripture: the Bengali verses are an ORIGINAL translation from the Hebrew and Greek, dedicated to
// the public domain (CC0). The only fully public-domain Bengali Bible (Carey, 1809) is in archaic
// Sadhu-bhasha; a modern rendering is both more readable and keeps this work uniformly CC0. The
// Bengali needs a fluent, scholarly proofread before print. English scripture is the public-domain
// Berean Standard Bible.

